        					This is good news.  Like Zehr says though, how can you say no to them talking about it.<br />
        <br />
        My only concern though is if Kitchener and Waterloo amalgamate (which is a logical choice) then what happens on a regional level?  Do things fall apart?  Will Cambridge and the Townships always feel like they are being &quot;ganged up against&quot; by a joint K-W?  Joining Kitchener and Waterloo could have a tough effect on Regional politics.  I don't know a ton about how it works, would it?
